{"entity": "Grape", "type": "naturalobject", "description": "Grape, scientifically known as a woody vine plant of the genus Vitis, is native to Europe, West Asia, and North Africa and is cultivated globally for its edible fruit, wine production, and medicinal applications derived from its roots and vines. It is a major economic fruit crop in regions such as Shanghai, Zhejiang, and Jiangsu, often grown under protected cultivation and celebrated in local festivals. In Anhui, grape is also cultivated within economic orchards, highlighting its significance in regional agriculture. The crop is widely covered in agricultural manuals, which include dedicated sections on disease management, pest control, and seasonal cultivation schedules.

